<BLOCK1><TI>CLAIM OF THE DEFENDANT(S) BRINGING THE COUNTERCLAIM</TI>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>1:</N><TI>STATEMENT OF FACTS</TI>
<P>1 The Defendant recites the facts and adopts the definitions contained in the Statement of Defence herein.</P>
<P>2 The Defendant pleads Section 45 of the Builder's Lien Act.</P>
<P>3 The Plaintiff and the principal of the Plaintiff, Alfredo Hermano (the &ldquo;Principal of the Plaintiff&rdquo;), did, as is described in the Statement of Defence herein, knowingly cause a false Claim of Lien to be filed.</P>
<P>4 The Plaintiff and the Principal of the Plaintiff knew, or should have known, at the time the false Claim of Lien was filed, that the stated claim far exceeded t he actual claim of the Plaintiff.</P>
<P>5 The Plaintiff and the Principal of the Plaintiff were responsible for the issuance of the false Declaration. The Defendant, acting reasonably, did not make payment under the Contract subsequent to the false Declaration, because:
<P1>a) of the uncertainty created when it (earned that the Declaration was false; and</P1>
<P1>b) by reason of the refusal of the Plaintiff and its Principal, Alfredo Hermano, to respond to its requests for an explanation regarding the false Declaration and for an accounting.</P1></P>
<P>6 The Plaintiff and its Principal, Alfredo Hermano, have refused to complete their obligations under the Contract which is the subject of this proceeding. They have maintained the Claim of Lien and this action with reckless indifference to the legitimate interests of the Defendant.</P>
<P>7 The Defendant, Lengara Ventures inc., has suffered loss, costs and damages by reason of the aforesaid actions of the Plaintiff, NGC Management Ltd. and its Principal, Alfredo Hermano, including:
<P1>a) Costs incurred by the Defendant in clearing a total of approximately 15 lien claims filed against the subject Lands; and</P1>
<P1>b) Damages by reason of the inordinate delay of the Plaintiff in completion of the subject Contract in breach of the terms of Contract resulting in, among other matters, the loss of an anchor tenant for a portion of the Lands;</P1></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>2:</N><TI>RELIEF SOUGHT</TI>
<P>1 Judgment for the costs and expenses incurred by the Defendant of and relating to the clearing of the title;</P>
<P>2 Punitive Damages; and</P>
<P>3 Costs of this proceeding on a special costs basis;</P></BLOCK2>
