<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>NOTICE OF APPEAL FROM MASTER, REGISTRAR OR SPECIAL REFEREE</UNDER></TI>
<P>WHEREAS on July 24, 2017. Master Muir made the following &square; decision &timesb; orders:
<P1>1. The Plaintiff's claim is dismissed;</P1>
<P1>2. The Letter of Credit, posted as security for release of the lien registered by the Plaintiff, be returned to the issuing bank, Canadian Western Bank; and</P1>
<P1>3. Costs of the application to the Defendant.</P1></P>
<P>TAKE NOTICE that the Plaintiff, NGC Management Ltd., appeals from that &square; decision &timesb; order on the following grounds:
<P1>1. the learned Master misapprehended or did not consider relevant evidence;</P1>
<P1>2. the learned Master considered inadmissible evidence;</P1>
<P1>3. the learned Master misapplied or did not consider the relevant law;</P1>
<P1>4. the learned Master misapprehended or did not consider the submissions of counsel; and</P1>
<P1>5. such further and other grounds as counsel may advise.</P1></P>
<P>This appeal will be heard at 9:45 am on October 24, 2017 at the courthouse at 800 Smithe Street, Vancouver, BC, by the presiding judge.</P>
<P>The appellant estimates that the hearing of the appeal wilt take 2 hours.</P>
<P>Date: 04/Aug/2017</P>
<P>&ellip35; Signature of lawyer for appellant,</P>
<P>Garrett Munroe</P></BLOCK1>
