<BLOCK1><TI>NOTICE OF APPLICATION</TI>
<P><EM>[Rule 22-3 of the Supreme Court Civil Rules applies to all forms.]</EM></P>
<P>Name(s) of applicant(s): LENGARA VENTURES INC.</P>
<P>To: The Plaintiff and its Solicitor</P>
<P>And to: Harrigan Rentals &amp; Equipment Ltd. and its Solicitor</P>
<P>And to: Rona Revy Inc., 4361814 Canada Inc. and their Solicitor</P>
<P>TAKE NOTICE that an application will be made by the applicant(s) to the presiding judge or master at the courthouse at THE LAW COURTS 651 CARNARVON ST. NEW WESTMINSTER V3M 1C9 British Columbia, on <BOLD>Thursday, August 12, 2010</BOLD> at 9:45 a.m. for the order(s) set out in Part 1 below.</P>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>1:</N><TI>ORDER(S) SOUGHT</TI>
<P><EM>[Using numbered paragraphs, set out the order(s) that will be sought at the application and indicate against which party(ies) the order(s) is(are) sought.]</EM></P>
<P>1. For an order authorizing payments by the Defendant to Rona Revy Inc. and Harrigan Rentals &amp; Equipment Ltd. in those amounts claimed by them pursuant to Claims of Lien Nos. XXXXXXXXXX and XXXXXXXXXX, such payments being on account of contracts with the Plaintiff, and for a further Order that the Plaintiff's Claim of Lien No. XXXXXXXXXX alone shall be discharged upon security being posted in accordance with the terms described in the Order attached hereto as Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo;, or on such other terms as this court shall direct.</P>
<P>2. Alternatively, the Applicant seeks an order in the form attached hereto as Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo;;</P>
<P>3. In the further alternative, the Applicant seeks an order substantially in the form attached hereto as Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo; provided that the security to be posted shall be in such other amount or amounts or on such other terms as this Honourable Court shall direct;</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>2:</N><TI>FACTUAL BASIS</TI>
<P><EM>[Using numbered paragraphs, set out a brief summary of the facts supporting the application.]</EM></P>
<P>1. The Plaintiff was the project manager and a contractor to the Defendant owner, and claims $399,417.36 against the lands owned by the Defendant (the &ldquo;Lands&rdquo;) pursuant to a Claim of Lien No. XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>2. Rona Revy Inc. (&ldquo;Rona&rdquo;) was a subcontractor to the Plaintiff and claims $21,727.03 against the lands pursuant to Claim of Lien No. XXXXXXXXXX. Rona claims through the Plaintiff and the sum claimed by it therefore forms part of the sum claimed by the Plaintiff.</P>
<P>3. Harrigan Rentals &amp; Equipment Ltd. (&ldquo;Harrigan&rdquo;) was a subcontractor to the Plaintiff and claims $57,648.11 against the lands pursuant to Claim of Lien No. XXXXXXXXXX Harrigan claims through the Plaintiff and the sum claimed by it therefore forms part of the sum claimed by the Plaintiff.</P>
<P>4. 4361814 Canada Inc. (&ldquo;4361814&rdquo;) is the successor in interest to Rona and has initiated legal proceedings in Action No. VLC-S-S-104836 to enforce Claim of Lien XXXXXXXXXX and has filed Certificate of Pending Litigation No. XXXXXXXXXX.</P>
<P>5. The claims of Rona (and its successor in interest, 4361814) and Harrigan have been previously admitted by the Plaintiffs representative.</P>
<P>6. The Defendant seeks an order enabling it to pay the admitted claims of Rona, 4361814, and Harrigan in order to obtain a discharge of all claims filed by them, and to discharge the claim of lien and Certificate of Pending Litigation filed by the Plaintiff upon securing the balance of its claim (net of the amounts paid to Rona, 4361814, and Harrigan).</P>
<P><EM>[If any party sues or is sued in a representative capacity, identify the party and describe the representative capacity.]</EM></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>3:</N><TI>LEGAL BASIS</TI>
<P><EM>[Using numbered paragraphs, specify any rule or other enactment relied on and provide a brief summary of any other legal arguments on which the applicant(s) intend(s) to rely in support of the orders sought. If appropriate, include citation of applicable cases.]</EM></P>
<P>1 The Applicant relies on Section 24 of the <EM>Builder's Lien Act</EM> and the inherent jurisdiction of this Honourable Court;</P></BLOCK2>
