<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Gary Walker, businessman, c/o #201, 20353&mdash;64<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue, in the Township of Langley, in the Province of British Columbia, make oath and say that::</P>
<P>1. I am the president of the Defendant, Lengara Ventures Inc. (the &ldquo;Company&rdquo;), and as such have personal knowledge of the facts and matters hereinafter deposed to save and except where stated to upon information and belief and where so stated I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am authorized to swear this Affidavit on behalf of the Defendant.</P>
<P>3. The sum of $323,585.35 (the &ldquo;Funds&rdquo;) were paid into court on August 30, 2010 by the Defendant as security for the Plaintiffs Claim of Lien Number XXXXXXXXXX &ldquo;Lien&rdquo;) pursuant to the Order of the Master of the Court dated August 13, 2010.</P>
<P>4. The Company is actively engaged in the business of property development in conjunction with related companies which operate auto body repair shops and requires access to its Funds for the operation of its business.</P>
<P>5. This application to substitute a Letter of Credit for the Funds in Court as security for the Lien is permitted by the terms of the Order.</P>
<P>6. The Defendant has, through its solicitor, requested that the Plaintiff consent to an order for the substitution of the Funds with a Letter of Credit, but to date the Plaintiff has not agreed to the same. No reasons have been given for this refusal.</P>
<P>7. This Affidavit is sworn in support of an application pursuant to Section 24 of the <EM>Builders Lien Act</EM> for an Order that the Order dated August 13, 2010 shall be varied by permitting the Defendant to provide a Letter of Credit issued by Canadian Western Bank, a chartered Canadian bank, in substitution for the Funds paid into court on August 30, 2010.</P>
