<BLOCK1><TI>NOTICE OF APPLICATION</TI>
<P>Name of applicant: Lengara Ventures Inc.</P>
<P>To: The Plaintiff and its Solicitor</P>
<P>TAKE NOTICE that an application will be made by the applicant to the presiding judge or master at the courthouse at Vancouver on January 13, 2011 at 9:45 a.m. for the orders set out in Part 1 below.</P>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>1:</N><TI>ORDERS SOUGHT</TI>
<P>1) An order that the security provided pursuant to the Order dated August 13, 2010 (the &ldquo;Order&rdquo;) shall be varied to permit the posting of a Letter of Credit in substitution for the funds held in court as security for the Plaintiff's Claim of Lien pursuant to the terms set out in the Order attached hereto as Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo;.</P>
<P>2) An order that the funds held in court, together with interest, if any, deposited with this Honourable Court in accordance with the Order shall be paid out to the Defendant, Lengara Ventures Inc., c/o Rosberg Sawatzky LLP, Barristers &amp; Solicitors, of #201, 20353 - 64<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue, Langley, B.C. V2Y 1N5, upon posting of the Letter of Credit in the form attached.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2 LABEL="Part"><N>2:</N><TI>FACTUAL BASIS</TI>
<P>1. The sum of $323,585.35 (the &ldquo;Funds&rdquo;) were paid into court on August 30, 2010 pursuant to the Order of the Master of the Court dated August 13, 2010.</P>
<P>2. The Company is actively engaged in the business of property development in conjunction with related companies which operate auto body repair shops and requires access to its Funds for the operation of its business.</P>
<P>3. This application to substitute a Letter of Credit for the Funds in Court as security for the Plaintiff's Claim of Lien number XXXXXXXXXX is permitted by the terms of the Order.</P>
<P>4. The Defendant has, through its solicitor, requested that the Plaintiff consent to an order to substitute a Letter of Credit for the Funds, but to date the Plaintiff has not agreed to the same. No reasons have been given for this refusal.</P></BLOCK2>
