<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Gary Walker, businessman, c/o #201, 20353 - 64<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue, in the Township of Langley, in the Province of British Columbia, make oath and say that:</P>
<P>1. I am the president of the Defendant, Lengara Ventures Inc. (&ldquo;Lengara&rdquo;), and as such have personal knowledge of the facts and matters hereinafter deposed to save and except where stated to upon information and belief and where so stated I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I have been authorized to swear this Affidavit on behalf of the Defendant.</P>
<P>3. I have read the Statement of Defence on behalf of the Defendant in these proceedings and verily believe the facts set forth therein to be true.</P>
<P>4. At all times relevant to these proceedings, the Defendant has been the owner of the lands and premises located at 3410 Lougheed Hwy, Vancouver, BC and presently legally described as Lot 1 Block 1 Section 38 Town of Hastings Suburban Lands Plan BCP43119 (the &ldquo;Lands&rdquo;).</P>
<P>5. The Plaintiff NGC Management Ltd (&ldquo;NGC&rdquo;) agreed with the Defendant that it would provide services for the management of the construction of the improvement to the Lands, including the provision of labour, materials, and other services by the Plaintiff and by subcontractors to the Plaintiff.</P>
<P>6. The improvement consisted of the construction of a commercial building and related improvements to the Lands (collectively the &ldquo;Improvement&rdquo;).</P>
<P>7. The operating mind behind the operations of NGC was at all relevant times Alfredo Hermano. He told me that he owned the Plaintiff and managed all aspects of its operations.</P>
<P>8. On December 26, 2009, I, on behalf of Lengara, met with Mr. Hermano, on behalf of NGC. At this meeting, the Plaintiff and the Defendant agreed, among other matters, that the Plaintiff was required to provide a statutory declaration to the Defendant in respect of the invoices issued by the Plaintiff to the Defendant upon substantial completion of the Improvement, prior to payment of those invoices by the Defendant.</P>
<P>9. When I met with Mr. Hermano on December 26, 2009, he assured me that all subcontractors to NGC were to be paid by NGC prior to the request for final payment of the agreed amounts which were to become due to NGC upon substantial completion of the Improvement, and that the Improvement was to be completed by January 25, 2010.</P>
<P>10. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; is a copy of the document signed by me on behalf of Lengara, and by Mr. Hermano on behalf of NGC, dated December 26, 2009 (the &ldquo;Contract&rdquo;).</P>
<P>11. On or about January 15, 2010, Lengara paid the balance of all invoices issued to that date by NGC pursuant to the Contract, for services to that date to the Improvement (the &ldquo;Progress Payment&rdquo;).</P>
<P>12. After the Progress Payment of January 15, 2010, Mr. Hermano caused NGC to issue further invoices for services provided by the Plaintiff to the Improvement, pursuant to the Contract. The invoices were dated February 2, 2010, March 9, 2010, and March 9, 2010, respectively. The total of the amounts invoiced by the Plaintiff to the Defendant pursuant to the three invoices was the sum of $104,648.91 (collectively the &ldquo;invoices&rdquo;). Copies of the Invoices are attached and marked as Exhibits &ldquo;B&rdquo;, &ldquo;C&rdquo; and &ldquo;D&rdquo; respectively.</P>
<P>13. Mr. Hermano executed a statutory declaration dated the 24<SUP>th</SUP> of February, 2010, required by the Contract, and provided it to me, in conjunction with a request for payment of the Invoices totaling $104,648.91. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo; is a copy of the Statutory Declaration executed by Mr. Hermano.</P>
<P>14. The Statutory Declaration included the following declaration:
<QUOTE><P><EM>that all accounts for labour, subcontracts, products, services, and construction machinery and equipment which have been incurred directly by the Contractor in the performance of the work as required by the Contract, and for which the Owner might in any way be held responsible, have been paid in full as required by the Contract up to and including the latest progress payment received, as identified above, except for</EM>:</P>
<P><EM>1) holdback monies properly retained</EM>,</P>
<P><EM>2) payments deferred by agreement, or</EM></P>
<P><EM>3) amounts withheld by reason of legitimate dispute which have been identified to the party or parties, from whom payment has been withheld</EM>.</P></QUOTE>
(the &ldquo;Declaration&rdquo;)</P>
<P>15. The Declaration made by Mr. Hermano was false. On the date the Declaration was made and on the date it was provided to the Defendant there were at least two subcontractors to the Plaintiff who had issued invoices to the Plaintiff for services to the Improvement prior to the latest Progress Payment, which invoices were not then paid, and for which the Defendant could be held responsible. The unpaid amounts to two of these subcontractors then totaled $75, 332.01 (the &ldquo;Unpaid Sub-Contracts&rdquo;).</P>
<P>16. I verily believe that Mr. Hermano must have been aware of the Unpaid Sub-Contracts when he made the Declaration because he was responsible to manage all of the business of NGC.</P>
<P>17. On becoming aware of the Unpaid Sub-Contracts I advised Mr. Hermano that Lengara was prepared to pay the amounts properly due to NGC pursuant to the Contract subject to satisfactory arrangements for payment of the Unpaid Sub-Contracts. Notwithstanding, the Plaintiff and its principal, Mr. Hermano, refused to make arrangements to pay the Unpaid Sub-Contracts and NGC caused a lien to be filed against the Lands, claiming the amount of $399,417.36.</P>
<P>18. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a Claim of Lien which was filed against the Lands under No. XXXXXXXXXX on March 12, 2010, executed by Mr. Hermano on behalf of NGC, claiming the amount of $399,417.36 (the &ldquo;NGC Lien&rdquo;).</P>
<P>19. NGC's claims herein as appears from the NGC Lien and the Statement of Claim in these proceedings is in the sum of $399,417.36 for services allegedly provided to the Improvement on the Lands.</P>
<P>20. No invoice for the amount claimed pursuant to the NGC Lien and herein was received by Lengara prior to the filing of the NGC Lien. NGC purported to provide invoices for the amounts covering the lien amount by letter dated March 15, 2010 after the NGC Lien was filed. A copy of that letter is attached hereto as Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;.</P>
<P>21. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a Claim of Lien which was filed against the Lands by Rona Revy Inc. (&ldquo;Rona&rdquo;) under No. CA1517383 on April 9, 2010. Rona was a subcontractor to NCG and claimed through NGC.</P>
<P>22. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the Claim of Lien which was filed against the Lands by Harrigan Rentals &amp; Equipments Ltd. (&ldquo;Harrigan&rdquo;) under No. XXXXXXXXXX on April 8, 2010. Harrigan was a subcontractor to NGC and claimed through NGC.</P>
<P>23. The lien claimants, Rona and Harrigan, described in Exhibits &ldquo;H&rdquo; and &ldquo;I&rdquo; contracted directly with NGC and were subcontractors to NGC for the provisions of material or services to the Improvements on the Lands.</P>
<P>24. Lengara has paid the sums claimed by Rona by its successor in interest, 4361814 Canada Inc., in the amount of $21,727.03, and the sums claimed by Harrigan in the amount of $57,648.11 (in each case to counsel acting for such claimant) on the basis that NGC authorized such payment on account of its contract with each of those subcontractors and that such amounts were to be deducted from the amount to be secured in respect of the Plaintiff's claim of lien. Attached hereto as Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo; is a copy of a letter dated August 13, 2010, to counsel for NGC, confirming the foregoing.</P>
<P>25. A total of 15 lien claims, excluding the NGC Lien, were asserted against the Lands, on or after completion of the Improvement. Much time was spent and costs incurred, from April through August 2010, to settle and discharge the liens, including the NGC Lien, from the Lands. Attached hereto as Exhibit &ldquo;K&rdquo; is a schedule of the said 15 claims of liens asserted against the Lands.</P>
<P>26. The Defendant also incurred significant costs and loss relating to:
<P1>a. the failure of the Plaintiff to complete the Improvement on time;</P1>
<P1>b. the refusal of the Plaintiff to properly comply with its obligations under the Contract;</P1>
<P1>c. the refusal of the Plaintiff, and Mr. Hermano, to provide all records in its possession relating to the project to the Defendant, despite demand;</P1>
<P1>d. the filing of the NGC Lien; and</P1>
<P1>e. the loss of an achor tenant who backed out of a lease because of the lien claims, in particular the NGC Lien, filed against the Lands.</P1></P>
<P>27. The loss and damages suffered in connection with the loss of the anchor tenant referred to in the proceeding paragraph were not known to be significant until early 2011 when the Defendant, despite making reasonable efforts, was unable to secure any tenant for the space the anchor tenant was to lease. That space remains without any tenant to date, at a rental loss of about $6,000 per month.</P>
<P>28. I make this Affidavit for the orders allowing the Defendant to file the Counterclaim and Third Party Notice attached as Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo; and Schedule &ldquo;B&rdquo; respectively to the Defendant's Notice of Application dated March 5, 2012, and for security for costs, and for no improper purpose.</P>
