<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, CLAUDINE AGUILLON, Legal Assistant, c/o #201, 20353 - 64<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue, in the Township of Langley, in the Province of British Columbia, make oath and say that:</P>
<P>1. I am a legal assistant at Rosberg Sawatzky LLP, solicitors for the Defendant, Lengara Ventures Inc. (&ldquo;Lengara&rdquo;), and as such have personal knowledge of the facts and matters hereinafter deposed to, save and except where such information is stated to be on information and belief, and I verily believe that information to be true.</P>
<P>2. Lengara was at all relevant times, and is, the owner of lands and premises located at 3410 Lougheed Hwy, Vancouver, British Columbia, legally described as PID 028-116-844, Lot 1 Block 1 Section 38 Township of Hastings Suburban Lands Plan BCP43119 (the &ldquo;Lands&rdquo;).</P>
<P>3. These proceedings concern allegations in respect of the provision of services by the Plaintiff, NGC Management Ltd. (&ldquo;NGC&rdquo;), in connection with the construction of a commercial building and related improvements to the Lands (the &ldquo;Improvement&rdquo;), claims of liens, and the execution of a false statutory declaration.</P>
<P>4. I have reviewed our files concerning this matter and set out the following chronology of steps and/or activities undertaken in connection with these proceedings.</P>
<P>5. On March 12, 2010, NGC filed a Claim of Lien against the title to the Lands under number XXXXXXXXXX in the amount of $399,417.36.</P>
<P>6. On April 8, 2010, Lengara delivered a Notice to Commence an Action to Enforce a Claim of Lien to NGC pursuant to section 33 of the <EM>Builder's Lien Act</EM>.</P>
<P>7. On April 8, 2010, Harrigan Rentals &amp; Equipment Ltd. filed a Claim of Lien against the Lands under number XXXXXXXXXX, in the amount of $57,648.11.</P>
<P>8. On April 9, 2010, Rona Revy Inc. filed a Claim of Lien against the Lands under number XXXXXXXXXX, in the amount of $21,727.03.</P>
<P>9. On April 19, 2010, NGC filed a Writ of Summons and Statement of Claim and registered a Certificate of Pending Litigation against the Lands, under number XXXXXXXXXX. NGC alleges breach of a written contract between NGC and Lengara, entered into on March 12, 2009, and claims the sum of $399,417.36, plus interest at the rate of 10% above the prime rate per annum, for services allegedly provided in relation to the Improvement. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>A</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the filed Writ of Summons and Statement of Claim.</P>
<P>10. On April 23, 2010, Lengara filed and served an Appearance and delivered a Demand for Discovery of Documents and Notice to Produce.</P>
<P>11. On April 26, 2010, NGC delivered a Demand for Discovery of Documents and Notice to Produce.</P>
<P>12. On May 17, 2010, Lengara filed a Statement of Defence, saying, among other things, that the written contract was amended from time to time by further agreements made between April 9, 2009 and December 26, 2009, and that Alfredo Hermano, the principal and operating mind behind the operations of NGC, knowingly executed a false statutory declaration that included a statement that alt subcontractors to NGC had been paid. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>B</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the filed Statement of Defence.</P>
<P>13. On June 30, 2010, NGC filed a Notice of Trial, setting the trial for 10 days commencing June 6, 2011.</P>
<P>14. On July 26, 2010, Lengara filed a Notice of Application returnable August 12, 2010, seeking orders authorizing payments to Rona Revy Inc. and Harrigan Rentals &amp; Equipment Ltd. in the amounts claimed, on account of contracts with NGC, and to discharge NGC's lien claim upon posting security,</P>
<P>15. On July 27, 2010, NGC delivered a List of Documents.</P>
<P>16. On August 13, 2010, the Honourable Master Donaldson made an order, by consent of the parties, canceling NGC's lien and Certificate of Pending Litigation, on payment into court by Lengara in the sum of $323,585.35, as security for NGC's claims.</P>
<P>17. On August 30, 2010, Lengara deposited funds in the amount of $323,585.35 into court in accordance with the Order of the Honourable Master Donaldson made August 13, 2010. Attached and marked collectively as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>C</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the Order of the Honourable Master Donaldson, together with the Registrar's Certificate certifying the deposit of funds,</P>
<P>18. From about April 2010 through August 2010, our office dealt with 15 lien claims, excluding that of NGC, asserted against the Lands.</P>
<P>19. On September 2, 2010, NGC delivered an Appointment to Examine For Discovery, to examine Gary Walker, as the representative for Lengara, on October 5, 2010. This discovery was cancelled on September 22, 2010.</P>
<P>20. On October 15, 2010, Lengara requested documents from NGC's List of Documents.</P>
<P>21. On October 28, 2010, NCG filed a Requisition to set a settlement conference for February 14, 2011. The same was delivered by fax sent November 19, 2010.</P>
<P>22. On November 23, 2010, Lengara delivered a List of Documents, We have no record of NGC making a request for a copy of the documents disclosed by Lengara.</P>
<P>23. By letter dated November 23, 2010, NGC provided copies of its listed documents to Lengara, as Lengara had requested.</P>
<P>24. On December 20, 2010, NGC filed a Requisition to set a trial management conference for April 27, 2011.</P>
<P>25. On December 31, 2010, Lengara filed an Application, returnable January 13, 2011, seeking to vary the Order of the Honourable Master Donaldson to substitute the security deposited with a letter of credit.</P>
<P>26. On January 13, 2011, the Honourable Master Tokarek varied the Order of the Honourable Master Donaldson to permit Lengara to deposit a letter of credit in substitution for the funds deposited. Despite request before the application was filed, NGC did not consent, and did not file responsive materials or attend at the hearing of this application.</P>
<P>27. On January 24, 2011, NGC filed a Requisition to reschedule the settlement conference from February 14, 2011, to April 8, 2011.</P>
<P>28. Pursuant to the Order of the Honourable Master Tokarek, Lengara deposited an Irrevocable Standby Letter of Credit with the Registrar of the Court Attached and marked collectively as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>D</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the order of the Honourable Master Tokarek, together with a copy of the Irrevocable Standby Letter of Credit deposited with the Registrar.</P>
<P>29. On April 5, 2011, Daniel Le Dressay, counsel for NGC, emailed Bruce Rosberg, counsel for Lengara, advising that NGC had filed a Notice of Intention to make a proposal pursuant to Division 1 of the <EM>Bankruptcy and Insolvency Act</EM>.</P>
<P>30. On April 6, 2011, NGC filed a Requisition to adjourn generally, by consent, the settlement conference set for April 8, 2011, the trial management conference set for April 27, 2011, and the trial set for June 6, 2011.</P>
<P>31. On December 7, 2011, NGC delivered an Appointment to Examine For Discovery, to examine Gary Walker, as the representative for Lengara, for February 13, 2013.</P>
<P>32. On March 23, 2012, NGC filed a Notice of Trial, resetting the trial, for 5 days, commencing June 3, 2013, with counsel for Lengara as to the date or reduced days, from 10 to 5 days.</P>
<P>33. On April 11, 2012, NGC filed a Notice of Case Planning Conference setting a case planning conference for August 29, 2012.</P>
<P>34. On April 24, 2012, Lengara filed a Notice of Application, seeking leave to file a Counterclaim and Third Party Notice, and for security for costs.</P>
<P>35. On July 6, 2012, the Honourable Mr. Justice Kelleher, among other things, granted Lengara leave to file a Counterclaim, and ordered NGC to post security for costs in the amount of $20,000 and stayed this proceeding until said security was posted. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>E</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the Order of the Honourable Mr. Justice Kelleher.</P>
<P>36. On or about July 19, 2012, our office was advised by Katelyn from Mr. Le Dressay's office, that the examination for discovery of Gary Walker set for February 13, 2013, would be cancelled.</P>
<P>37. On July 26, 2012, Lengara filed a Counterclaim, in accordance with the Order of the Honourable Mr. Justice Kelleher made July 6, 2012, and served the same by fax to Mr. Le Dressay, whose office faxed back the service copy of the letter covering the Counterclaim, with only the date of service written in as July 27, 2012.</P>
<P>38. On August 15, 2012, NGC served a Requisition filed August 14, 2012, adjourning, the case management conference set for August 29, 2012, generally by consent.</P>
<P>39. On November 9, 2012, NGC served a Requisition filed November 8, 2012, adjourning the trial set for June 3, 2013, generally by consent.</P>
<P>40. On February 22, 2016, NGC filed and served a Notice of Appointment or Change of Lawyer appointing Garrett Munroe to act as the lawyer for NGC in place of Mr, Le Dressay.</P>
<P>41. Our office has no record of, and I verily believe from my search of the registry, via Court Services Online on October 5, 2016, that to date:
<P1>a. NGC had not complied with the Order of Mr. Justice Kelleher made July 6, 2012, to post security for costs; and</P1>
<P1>b. NGC had not filed a Response to Counterclaim.</P1>
Attached to this affidavit and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>F</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a Court Services Online File Summary Report showing the documents filed in these proceedings. The documents numbered 32 and 34 are the requisitions referred to in paragraphs 38 and 39 above, adjourning the case management conference and trial.</P>
<P>42. I make this Affidavit in support of the application of Lengara to dismiss these proceedings for want of prosecution.</P>
