<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, CLAUDINE AGUILLON, Legal Assistant, c/o #201, 20353 - 64<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue, in the Township of Langley, in the Province of British Columbia, make oath and say that:</P>
<P>1. I am a legal assistant at Rosberg Sawatzky LLP, solicitors for the Defendant, Lengara Ventures Inc. (&ldquo;Lengara&rdquo;), and as such have personal knowledge of the facts and matters hereinafter deposed to, save and except where such information is stated to be on information and belief, and I verily believe that information to be true.</P>
<P>2. Attached and marked collectively as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>A</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a Company Summary, dated December 13, 2016, and Corporate Information printed January 24, 2017, obtained through BC Registry Services Corporate Online, for NGC Constructors Ltd., known until November 15, 2013, as NGC Management Ltd. the plaintiff herein (&ldquo;NGC&rdquo;).</P>
<P>3. Attached and marked collectively as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>B</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the Order Approving Proposal, in the Matter of the Proposal of NGC, in the Supreme Court of British Columbia, Vancouver Registry, No. B110435, together with a copy of the Report of Trustee on Proposal.</P>
<P>4. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>C</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of pages downloaded from NGC's website: ngc.build. Among other things, the following information is represented therein:
<P1>a. NGC is an owner's representative, general contractor and construction management company with a portfolio of projects across Western Canada valued up to $15 million.</P1>
<P1>b. NGC acted and/or is acting as an owner's representative, general contractor and/or construction manager for 13 projects, with a total value of $41M.</P1>
<P1>c. Start and/or completion or estimated completion dates are noted for only 4 projects: September 2014; January 2015; March 2015; and Summer 2015.</P1>
<P1>d. NGC opened a new office in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan in May 2014.</P1>
<P1>e. NGC opened a new office in Ontario in September 2015, to be managed by Alfredo Hermano, in the process of moving with his family, would continue in his role as CEO of NGC and be on a plane a lot ensuring NGC's Western Canadian projects, clients and employees got the support they needed through the transition.</P1></P>
<P>5. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>D</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of pages downloaded from NGC's Facebook page on January 24, 2017. The following information is posted:
<P1>a. NGC started a construction project (a Brown's Social House base building) in Weyburn, SK, which project was not one of the 13 highlighted, but no start and/or completion or estimated completion dates are noted, on NGC's website referred to the preceding paragraph in late 2014; the same was completed in July 2015. (July 13, 2015)</P1>
<P1>b. &ldquo;2014 was a great year, full of growth, and [NGC was] poised for more growth in 2015.&rdquo; (January 9, 2015)</P1>
<P1>c. NGC &ldquo;just completed construction of a brand new Milestones Grill &amp; Bar... in Abbotsford, BC&rdquo;, which project was one of the 13 highlighted on NGC's website referred to in the preceding paragraph. (June 18, 2014)</P1>
<P1>d. NGC was &ldquo;awarded the construction of a new Carl's Jr. in downtown Vancouver&rdquo; which project does not appear to be highlighted on NGC's website referred to in the preceding paragraph. (October 18, 2012)</P1>
<P1>e. &ldquo;NGC was recently awarded the Goldstream &amp; Millstream Village projects in Langford, BC&rdquo; projects do not appear to be highlighted on NGC's website referred to in the preceding paragraph. (September 21, 2012)</P1></P>
<P>6. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>E</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a BC Court Services Online E-search conducted January 24, 2017, searching &ldquo;NGC&rdquo; in Civil By Party Name. The same shows NGC as a party in eighty-four civil proceedings, commenced from January 2008 to January 2017.</P>
<P>7. The following exhibits are a true copy of documents downloaded via Court Services Online on January 24, 2017, concerning some of the proceedings, as described below, that NGC is named as a party in:
<P1>a. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>F</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a File Summary Report showing the Case Basics, Parties, Documents, and Hearing and Results, Details of Documents filed (some), and pleadings filed (some), in proceedings commenced by NGC in the Supreme Court of British Columbia, Vancouver Registry No. S122224, on March 26, 2012, seeking among other things, judgment in the amount of $386,803.72. The File Summary Report, Documents tab, shows steps taken in the proceedings by NGC in 2012, 2013, 2014, and 2015, including in May 2014, setting the matter for trial in June 2015, and a Consent Order made September 13, 2012, ordering payment of security for costs, which payment appears to have been made given the terms of the order and further steps appearing to have been taken in the proceedings.</P1>
<P1>b. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>G</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a File Summary Report showing the Case Basics, Parties, Documents, and Hearing and Results, Details of Documents filed (some), and pleadings filed (some), in proceedings commenced by NGC in the Supreme Court of British Columbia, Smithers Registry No. 17103, on February 6, 2015, seeking among other things, judgment in the amount of $803,522.22. The File Summary Report, Documents tab, shows steps taken in the proceedings by NGC in 2015 and 2016.</P1>
<P1>c. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>H</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a File Summary Report showing the Case Basics, Parties, Documents, and Hearing and Results and pleadings filed (some), in small claims proceedings commenced against NGC in the Provincial Court of British Columbia (Small Claims Court) Robson Square Provincial Court Registry File Number 1551557, on March 12, 2015; NGC filed a Counterclaim on March 28, 2015. The File Summary Report, Documents tab, shows applications made, and attendances, by NGC in the proceedings in 2015 and 2016, resulting in an agreed to Payment Order and Dismissal Order on the Counterclaim.</P1>
<P1>d. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>I</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a File Summary Report showing the Case Basics, Parties, Documents, and Hearing and Results and pleadings filed (some), in small claims proceedings commenced by NGC in the Provincial Court of British Columbia (Small Claims Court) Robson Square Provincial Court Registry File Number 1553059, on August 13, 2015, seeking judgement in the amount of $25,000, plus interest and costs.</P1>
<P1>e. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>J</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a File Summary Report showing the Case Basics, Parties, Documents, and Hearing and Results and pleadings filed (some), in proceedings commenced by NGC in the Supreme Court of British Columbia, Penticton Registry Fife No. 041270, on September 29, 2016.</P1>
<P1>f. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>K</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a File Summary Report showing the Case Basics, Parties, Documents, and Hearing and Results and pleading filed, in proceedings commenced by NGC in the Supreme Court of British Columbia, New Westminster Registry Court File No. NEW-S-S-186356, on November 24, 2016, claiming, among other things, for debt totaling $758,076.96.</P1></P>
<P>8. Lengara's Notice of Application, seeking dismissal of these proceedings for want of prosecution, and affidavits in support, was delivered to counsel for NGC on October 26, 2016. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>L</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of the Package Tracking receipt confirming delivery.</P>
<P>9. Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;<BOLD>M</BOLD>&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a true copy of a printout of Court Order Interests Rates downloaded from the Courts of British Columbia website on January 25, 2017, which sets out the banker's prime rate. Using Exhibit &ldquo;M&rdquo;, I have calculated the average rate of annual interest claimed by NGC in these proceedings as set out in the Statement of Claim (&ldquo;interest at the rate of 10% above the prime rate per annum&rdquo;) for the period from the filing of the Statement of Claim in April 2010 to date to be approximately 12.918%. On the amount of $323,585.35, secured for NGC's claim, this results in a claim for interest of approximately $41,800.00 per annum, or approximately $282,150.00 to date. On the amount claimed in the Statement of Claim, $399,417.36, the annual interest would be approximately $51,596.00, or approximately $348,277.00 to date.</P>
