<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Maarten Koorn, businessman, c/o Munroe &amp; Company, 2207 - 2850 Shaughnessy Street, in the City of Port Coquitlam, in the Province of British Columbia, SWEAR (OR AFFIRM) THAT:
<P1>1. I am the Chief Operating Officer of the plaintiff company and as such I have personal knowledge of the facts and matters referred to in this affidavit except where the same are stated to be made upon information and belief and where so stated I verily believe the same to be true.</P1>
<P1>2. The plaintiff, NGC Management Ltd., is now known as NGC Constructors Ltd. (&ldquo;NGC&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>3. I have reviewed Affidavit #2 of Claudine Aguillon.</P1>
<P1>4. NGC has published information relating to several projects to highlight its capacity for business success and future growth plans on the website www.ngc.build. This content is aspirational, promotional information.</P1>
<P1>5. It is common industry practice to engage in online self -promotion to attract further business opportunities.</P1>
<P1>6. It would be unusual and harmful to business to include details of a company's financial challenges on its website.</P1>
<P1>7. It is in part because of NGC's promotional efforts that NGC has very recently obtained a contract for a very large project. This project is many times larger than NGC's contract with Lengara. NGC is currently working on the contract and will make a substantial profit due to this project.</P1>
<P1>8. In response to paragraph 4(b) of Affidavit #2 of Claudine Aguillon, these 13 projects were spread out over a period of approximately 14 years. The value of the projects are rounded up and also includes the Lengara project for which NGC was not paid. Most of these projects had a margin of 2% to 3% so there was little money left over to recover the losses suffered due to Lengara's non-payment and pay for other costs such as overhead and legal expenses.</P1>
<P1>9. Due to the financial pressures largely caused by Lengara's non-payment of money owed to NGC, NGC had to make a Division 1 Proposal to Creditors under the <EM>Bankruptcy and Insolvency Act</EM> to obtain debt relief without going into bankruptcy.</P1>
<P1>10. NGC's Ontario office is based in Alfredo Hermano's home. There is negligible cost to operate this home office.</P1>
<P1>11. Similarly, NGC's Saskatoon office was only opened because NGC's estimator wanted to move to Saskatoon. He is NGC's only employee in Saskatchewan. The office is a sublease of a small space within an office and costs approximately $500 per mont h.</P1></P>
