<P>I, Samantha Riehs, legal assistant, c/o Munroe &amp; Company, 2207 - 2850 Shaughnessy Street, in the City of Port Coquitlam, in the Province of British Columbia, SWEAR (OR AFFIRM) THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a legal assistant with Munroe &amp; Company, the solicitors for the plaintiff, NGC Management Ltd. (&ldquo;NGC&rdquo;), and therefore I have personal knowledge of the facts and matters referred to in this affidavit except where the same are stated to be made upon information and belief and, whe re so stated, I verily believe the same to be true.</P>
<P>2. On January 21, 2017, Mr. Garrett Munroe, solicitor for the Plaintiff, served on Mr. Bruce Rosberg, solicitor for the Defendant, by fax and by email, a letter and Notice of Intention to Proceed. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit A&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter, Notice of Intention to Proceed, fax confirmation, and email confirmation.</P>
<P>3. On January 23, 2017, Mr. Munroe, on behalf of the Plaintiff, filed a Requisition paying into court the sum of $20,000.00 as security for costs pursuant to the Order of Mr. Justice Kelleher made July 6, 2012. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit B&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the Requisition and the Registrar's Certificate confirming payment of the funds into court.</P>
<P>4. On January 23, 2017, Mr. Munroe filed a Response to Counterclaim on behalf of the Plaintiff. On January 25, 2017, Ms. Laura Rychkun, a paralegal at Munroe &amp; Company, served on Mr. Rosberg, by fax and by email, the Plaintiffs Response to Counterclaim. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit C&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter, Response to Counterclaim, fax confirmation, and email confirmation.</P>
<P>5. Mr. Munroe has advised me, and I verily believe that on February 21, 2017 he served the following documents by hand to Mr. Rosberg:
<P1>a. a letter and Appointment to Examine for Discovery of Gary Walker, a representative of the Defendant. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit D&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter and Appointment to Examine for Discovery;</P1>
<P1>b. a letter and Demand for Particulars. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit E&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter and Demand for Particulars; and</P1>
<P1>c. a letter and unfiled Notice of Case Planning Conference. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit F&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter and unfiled Notice of Case Planning Conference.</P1></P>
<P>6. On February 23, 2017, Ms. Rychkun served on Mr. Rosberg, by fax and by legal alternative courier, a letter and filed Notice of Case Planning Conference. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit G&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter, filed Notice of Case Planning Conference, and fax confirmation.</P>
<P>7. On March 1, 2017, Mr. Munroe filed a Case Plan Proposal on behalf of the Plaintiff. On March 8, 2017, Mr. Munroe served on Mr. Rosberg, by fax and by legal alternative courier, a letter and the Plaintiff's Case Plan Proposal. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit H&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter, Case Plan Proposal, and fax confirmation.</P>
<P>8. On March 8, 2017, Mr. Munroe filed a Notice of Trial scheduling a 7-day trial of this matter commencing on April 3, 2018. On March 10, 2017, Mr. Munroe served on Mr. Rosberg, by fax and by legal alternative courier, a letter and filed Notice of Trial. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit I&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of the letter, Notice of Trial, and fax confirmation.</P>
<P>9. On April 4, 2017, Mr. Rosberg served our office with a letter and the Defendant's Amended Case Plan Proposal. Attached hereto and marked collectively as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit J&rdquo;</BOLD> are true copies of Mr. Rosberg's letter and the Defendant's Case Plan Proposal.</P>
<P>10. On April 5, 2017, Mr. Rosberg and Mr. Munroe attended a Case Planning Conference, and it was ordered that all steps be adjourned until the Defendant's Application is heard on June 15, 2017.</P>
<P>11. On April 6, 2017, I emailed Mainland Reporting Services and cancelled the examination for discovery of Gary Walker scheduled for April 19, 2017. Attached hereto and marked as &ldquo;<BOLD>Exhibit K&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of my email to Mainland Reporting Services.</P>
