<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>AFFIDAVIT</UNDER></TI>
<P>I, Maarten Koorn, business person and chief operating officer of NGC Management Ltd., 210 - 24 East 4th Avenue, in the City of Vancouver, in the Province of British Columbia, AFFIRM THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am chief operating officer for the plaintiff, NGC Management Ltd. (&ldquo;NGC&rdquo;), and therefore have personal knowledge of the facts and matters referred to in this affidavit except where the same are stated to be made upon information and belief and, where so stated, I verily believe the same to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am authorized by NGC to swear this Affidavit.</P>
<P>3. Shortly after July 24, 2017, I became aware of the reasons for judgment of Master Muir given on July 24, 2017 dismissing the action herein (the &ldquo;Decision&rdquo;). At all material times, NGC intended to pursue an appeal of the Decision. To that end, NGC retained Garrett Munroe to assist with the prosecution of that appeal (the &ldquo;Appeal&rdquo;), and I expected that Appeal to be filed and all necessary steps to be taken.</P>
<P>4. On November 21, 2017, I was surprised to discover for the first time that certain deadlines requiring completion and delivery of a statement of argument had not been met by Mr. Munroe. On this date, I also became aware for the first time that the defendant Lengara Ventures Inc. (&ldquo;Lengara&rdquo;) had brought an application to strike the Appeal, among other orders sought.</P>
<P>5. On November 21, 2017, I also first became aware at that time that Mr. Munroe has been ill for the past few months. Prior to this date, I was not aware of Mr. Munroe's illness nor was I aware of the deadline to deliver the statement of argument relating to the Appeal or that NGC had missed that deadline.</P>
<P>6. Between July and November 2017, I attempted to contact Mr. Munroe on a number of occasions in relation to the Appeal and ancillary matters. I also attempted to schedule appointments to meet with Mr. Munroe on a few occasions but was unable to successfully schedule an appointment with him. I was not aware of any particular cause for concern and so I simply continued to try to schedule a meeting.</P>
<P>7. It has always been and remains NGC's intention to pursue the Appeal. To that end, NGC intends to complete and deliver its statement of argument with the assistance of either Mr. Munroe or new counsel. In the event that Mr. Munroe is unable to assist promptly, NGC intends to retain other counsel to complete and deliver the statement of argument, all of which NGC hopes and expects to have completed within 4 weeks of today's date.</P>
